Detailed Description

Implementation details.

Exposes constants used to interact with the download manager's content provider. The constants URI ... STATUS are the names of columns in the downloads table.

Definition at line 58 of file Download.h.

static const base::String& gaia::net::Download::Impl::ACTION_DOWNLOAD_COMPLETED ( ) [static]

Broadcast Action: this is sent by the download manager to the app that had initiated a download when that download completes.

The download's content: uri is specified in the intent's data.

static const base::String& gaia::net::Download::Impl::ACTION_NOTIFICATION_CLICKED ( ) [static]

Broadcast Action: this is sent by the download manager to the app that had initiated a download when the user selects the notification associated with that download.

The download's content: uri is specified in the intent's data if the click is associated with a single download, or Downloads.CONTENT_URI if the notification is associated with multiple downloads. Note: this is not currently sent for downloads that have completed successfully.

static const base::String& gaia::net::Download::Impl::COLUMN_NO_INTEGRITY ( ) [static]

The name of the column containing the flags that indicates whether the initiating application is capable of verifying the integrity of the downloaded file.

When this flag is set, the download manager performs downloads and reports success even in some situations where it can't guarantee that the download has completed (e.g. when doing a byte-range request without an ETag, or when it can't determine whether a download fully completed).

Type: BOOLEAN

static int32_t gaia::net::Download::Impl::DESTINATION_CACHE_PARTITION ( ) [static]

This download will be saved to the download manager's private partition.

This is the behavior used by applications that want to download private files that are used and deleted soon after they get downloaded. All file types are allowed, and only the initiating application can access the file (indirectly through a content provider). This requires the android.permission.ACCESS_DOWNLOAD_MANAGER_ADVANCED permission.

static int32_t gaia::net::Download::Impl::DESTINATION_CACHE_PARTITION_NOROAMING ( ) [static]

This download will be saved to the download manager's private partition, as with DESTINATION_CACHE_PARTITION, but the download will not proceed if the user is on a roaming data connection.

static int32_t gaia::net::Download::Impl::DESTINATION_CACHE_PARTITION_PURGEABLE ( ) [static]

This download will be saved to the download manager's private partition and will be purged as necessary to make space.

This is for private files (similar to CACHE_PARTITION) that aren't deleted immediately after they are used, and are kept around by the download manager as long as space is available.

static int32_t gaia::net::Download::Impl::DESTINATION_EXTERNAL ( ) [static]

This download will be saved to the external storage.

This is the default behavior, and should be used for any file that the user can freely access, copy, delete. Even with that destination, unencrypted DRM files are saved in secure internal storage. Downloads to the external destination only write files for which there is a registered handler. The resulting files are accessible by filename to all applications.

static int32_t gaia::net::Download::Impl::DESTINATION_FILE_URI ( ) [static]

This download will be saved to the location given by the file URI in COLUMN_FILE_NAME_HINT.

static int32_t gaia::net::Download::Impl::DESTINATION_NON_DOWNLOADMANAGER_DOWNLOAD ( ) [static]

This download was completed by the caller (i.e., NOT downloadmanager) and caller wants to have this download displayed in Downloads App.

static int32_t gaia::net::Download::Impl::DESTINATION_SYSTEMCACHE_PARTITION ( ) [static]

This download will be saved to the system cache ("/cache") partition.

This option is only used by system apps and so it requires android.permission.ACCESS_CACHE_FILESYSTEM permission.

static int32_t gaia::net::Download::Impl::STATUS_LENGTH_REQUIRED ( ) [static]

This download cannot be performed because the length cannot be determined accurately.

This is the code for the HTTP error "Length Required", which is typically used when making requests that require a content length but don't have one, and it is also used in the client when a response is received whose length cannot be determined accurately (therefore making it impossible to know when a download completes).

static int32_t gaia::net::Download::Impl::STATUS_PRECONDITION_FAILED ( ) [static]

This download was interrupted and cannot be resumed.

This is the code for the HTTP error "Precondition Failed", and it is also used in situations where the client doesn't have an ETag at all.
